---
title: Chat Turn Sequence – Context Pipeline, LLM Execution & FSM Advancement
---
%% Caption: UML Sequence Diagram mapping the exact physical execution of a single chat turn 
%% through SalesChatbot.chat(), accurately reflecting the codebase order of operations:
%% context gathering -> intention analysis -> LLM request -> FSM progression.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    
    Note over Client,Analytics: DIAGRAM LEGEND<br/>Blue = Client/API/external | Orange = Core logic<br/>Green = Web routes | Purple = LLM providers<br/>Gray = Storage/analytics | dotted = conditional/async

    participant Client as Client (Browser)
    participant API as app.py (API Layer)
    participant Chatbot as SalesChatbot
    participant Analysis as analysis.py
    participant Flow as SalesFlowEngine
    participant Content as content.py
    participant Provider as providers/factory.py
    participant Store as "sessions/*.json (filesystem store)"
    participant Analytics as analytics (Performance/Session)

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
      Note over Client,API: Layer 0 — Client request
    end

    Client ->> API: POST /api/chat {session_id, user_message}
    activate API
    API ->> Chatbot: invoke chat(user_message)
    activate Chatbot

    rect rgb(220, 255, 220)
      Note over Chatbot,Content: Layer 1 — Context & Prompt Aggregation
    end

    opt current_stage == 'objection'
        Chatbot ->> Analysis: classify_objection(message, history)
        Analysis -->> Chatbot: objection_data
    end

    Chatbot ->> Flow: get_current_prompt(user_message)
    activate Flow
    Flow ->> Content: generate_stage_prompt(...)
    activate Content
    Content -->> Flow: composed_prompt
    deactivate Content
    Flow -->> Chatbot: system_prompt
    deactivate Flow

    Chatbot ->> Analysis: analyse_state(history, user_message)
    Analysis -->> Chatbot: state (intent mapping)
    Chatbot ->> Analytics: record_intent_classification()

    rect rgb(255, 245, 220)
      Note over Chatbot,Provider: Layer 2 — Provider Request & Fallback
    end

    Chatbot ->> Provider: chat(messages, stage)
    activate Provider
    alt Primary Provider responds
        Provider -->> Chatbot: llm_response
    else Rate limit / Timeout
        Provider ->> Provider: try fallback sequence (list_providers)
        Provider -->> Chatbot: fallback_response or error
    end
    deactivate Provider

    Chatbot ->> Flow: add_turn(user_message, bot_reply)
    Chatbot ->> Store: save_session() (JSON to disk)
    Chatbot ->> Analytics: log_stage_latency(latency_ms)

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
      Note over Chatbot,Flow: Layer 3 — FSM Advancement & Strategy Switching
    end

    Chatbot ->> Chatbot: _apply_advancement(user_message)
    activate Chatbot
    
    opt strategy == INTENT
        Chatbot ->> Chatbot: _detect_and_switch_strategy() (check linguistic signals)
    end

    Chatbot ->> Flow: get_advance_target(user_message)
    activate Flow
    Flow -->> Chatbot: target_stage (or None)
    deactivate Flow

    opt if target_stage distinct from current_stage
        Chatbot ->> Flow: advance(target_stage)
        Flow -->> Chatbot: updated_stage
        Chatbot ->> Analytics: record_stage_transition()
    end
    deactivate Chatbot

    Chatbot -->> API: ChatResponse object
    deactivate Chatbot
    
    API -->> Client: HTTP 200 {response JSON}
    deactivate API

    Note over Chatbot,Analytics: Operations strictly follow sequential order within `SalesChatbot.chat()`.
